description:
Too Many Accessories - A mod that allows you to increase your stats using slots for accessories and armor in vanilla mode, as well as using the hotbar and inventory.

It adds 8 new accessories crafted using Expert mode resources that allow you to increase your armor and accessories to exorbitant levels.

Accessory activator in vanilla mode (Vanity Accessory Enabler), when equipped in an active accessory slot, allows you to receive accessory/armor effects from vanilla accessory/armor slots;
Hot panel accessory activator (Hotbar Accessory Enabler), when equipped in an active accessory slot, allows you to receive accessory/armor effects from hotbar accessories/armor;
Accessory activator in the bottom row of inventory (Lowest Row Accessory Enabler), when equipped in an active accessory slot, allows you to obtain accessory/armor effects from accessories/armor in the bottom row of your inventory;
Accessory activator in the bottom two rows of inventory (Two Lowest Rows Accessory Enabler), when equipped in the active accessory slot, allows you to obtain accessory/armor effects from accessories/armor in the bottom two rows of your inventory;
Accessory activator in almost full inventory (Almost Full Inventory Acessory Enabler), when equipped in an active accessory slot, allows you to receive the effects of accessories/armor from accessories/armor in any inventory row except the top one (row below the hotbar);
Accessory activator in full inventory (Full Inventory Acessory Enabler), when equipped in an active accessory slot, allows you to receive the effects of accessories/armor from accessories/armor in any row of the inventory (except for the hot bar);
Full accessory activator (Total Accessory Enabler), when equipped in an active accessory slot, allows you to gain accessory/armor effects from any inventory slot, hotbar, or vanilla accessory/armor slots.
Chest accessory activator (Chest Accessory Enabler) must be configured by left clicking on any chest, piggy bank, safe or forge of the defender. Then equip it into your active accessory slot to have the contents of that chest added to your stats. It is limited by settings (default is disabled or set to 0) and each chest is only processed once, but you can share chests with other players.
Additionally, the chest accessory activator must be set up every time you enter a world (it doesn't save the chest it's on for common sense reasons), so every time you enter a world you need to open the accessory chest and use the activator chest accessories on it. This is a mod that does not aim to balance the game. Consider it a less cheating alternative to other similar mods.
Changes in version 0.6:

Added piggy bank accessory activators as an alternative to filling the entire inventory with accessories:
They completely replace the use of the main inventory slots for accessories, so you cannot use, for example, an accessory activator from the bottom row with an accessory activator for a piggy bank.
They can still be equipped together, but only the one found first will be used.
The order of activating accessories and searching for armor is as follows: vanilla accessory slots, vanilla armor slots, hotbar, and then either the piggy bank or inventory from the first row to the last.
The ability to change configuration on servers has also been temporarily changed (you must be the first player on the server to make changes).
